      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1605">
               <p>The son of a Swiss father who came to <placeName>England</placeName> about <date
                     when="1680">1680</date>, Vincent was baptized in <placeName>London</placeName>
                  on <date when="1693-12-12">Dec. 12, 1693</date>. He matriculated at Queen&apos;s
                  College, <placeName>Oxford</placeName> in <date when="1714-12">Dec. 1714</date>,
                  receiving the <seg ana="degree">BA</seg> in <date when="1718">1718</date>. He
                  proceeded that year to be ordained deacon <date when="1718-10-08">Oct. 8</date>,
                  married to <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1598.xml"/>Charity
                     Goodhew</persName> on <date when="1718-12-04">Dec. 4</date>, ordained priest in
                  the Church of <placeName>England</placeName> on <date when="1718-12-21">Dec.
                     21</date>, and appointed curate at <placeName>Sundridge, Kent</placeName>. In
                     <date when="1734">1734</date> he was made vicar of
                     <placeName>Shoreham</placeName>, where he remained to his death. Vincent and
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1598.xml"/>Charity</persName> had at
                  least a dozen children, several of whom appear in Wesley correspondence. Vincent
                  first met <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> in <date
                     when="1744-08">Aug. 1744</date>, being introduced through <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1622.xml"/>Henry Piers</persName>. His interest in and
                  support of the Methodist revival was intensified by the death of his son
                     <persName>Vincent</persName> in <date when="1746">1746</date>. Within a couple
                  of years Peronnet was one of the strongest supporters and confidants of both
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> and
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName>. See <hi
                     rend="italic">Alumni Oxonienses</hi>; Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>,
                  317–26; Batty, <hi rend="italic">Perronet</hi>; CCEd; <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>,
                  876; <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>,
                  269–70.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
